    {
      "id": 259,
      "type": "MarkdownNote",
      "pos": [
        -500,
        200
      ],
      "size": [
        400,
        520
      ],
      "flags": {},
      "order": 19,
      "mode": 0,
      "inputs": [],
      "outputs": [],
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "# HOW TO USE\n\n## GENERATE (default)\n1. Paste prompt into the CLIP Text Encode node.\n2. Leave the purple EDIT nodes greyed out.\n3. Queue Prompt.\n\n## EDIT AN IMAGE INSTEAD\nThe purple group (Load Image + VAEEncode) is BYPASSED by default (greyed out).\n\nTo turn edit mode ON:\n1. Click the **Load Image** node, press **Ctrl+B** (it un-greys).\n2. Click the **VAEEncode** below it, press **Ctrl+B** too.\n3. On Load Image, click 'choose file to upload' and pick your image.\n4. **REWIRE:** drag from **VAEEncode -> LATENT** (output, right side)\n   into **KSampler (Stage 1) -> latent_image** (input, left side).\n   This replaces the wire coming from EmptySD3LatentImage.\n5. Set that Stage-1 KSampler **denoise** to about **0.5**\n   (0.4 = subtle change, 0.6 = heavy change).\n6. Queue. Your image runs through all 3 refine stages.\n\nTo go BACK to generating:\n- Drag **EmptySD3LatentImage -> LATENT** back into\n  **KSampler (Stage 1) -> latent_image**.\n- Set that KSampler denoise back to **1.0**.\n- Ctrl+B the two purple nodes again to bypass them.\n\n## FIX WATER/DROPLETS\nDENOISE GUIDE (lower = gentler, more faithful):\n- Stage 2 refine (id 207): 0.35 default. Raise toward 0.45 for MORE\n  detail/droplet fixing, lower to 0.25 if it looks overcooked.\n- Stage 3 cleanup (id 210): 0.2 default. This just smooths \u2014 keep it low.\nIf the image looks too contrasty/plastic/over-sharp: LOWER stage 2.\n\n## IF IT RUNS OUT OF MEMORY\nLower the **ImageScale** node from 2432x1664 to 2048x1400."
      ]
    }
